{"name": "Bardic Archetype: Comedian", "type": "archetype", "img": "icons/magic/control/mouth-smile-deception-purple.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Subclass for the @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.classes.MGOXKZCFR46MSF08]{Bard} class.</p><p>Comedians are bards Bards that thrive on lighthearted and uplifting performance. Their aim is to treat their audiences to a laugh and help them put their cares aside for a while. Ironically, you might not want to fall completely for their jolly demeanor - let your guard fall too far and you might just end up the unwitting volunteer for their next prank!</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "identifier": "bard-comedian", "classIdentifier": "bard", "classDetails": "<h3>Bardic Archetype: Comedian</h3><p><i>Unlock:</i> Have the Bard Starter Abilities.</p><hr/><p>&#x1F193; Given Abilities: @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.XS4831HQBSH7W2M4]{Theme: Levity}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.UT2MT6HXQ4PUJKCF]{People Person}</p><hr/><h3>Comedian Abilities</h3><p>When taking a level in Comedian, you may choose from the following abilities: </p><hr/><p>Options: @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.TJ4VKZYFH31W9X3V]{Prop Weapons}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.7RD3VKTZ5NAWVBRS]{Self-Insert}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.YNYRG1OSHNZ1HDC1]{Bloopers}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.OS4PU32OTOKG859U]{Slapstick}</p>"}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "E1U48LF829LGUWPO", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
{"name": "Bardic Archetype: Tragedian", "type": "archetype", "img": "icons/magic/control/fear-fright-white.webp", "system": {"description": {"value": "<p>Subclass for the @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.classes.MGOXKZCFR46MSF08]{Bard} class.</p><p>Tragedians are Bards whose work guides others through the somber and heartbreaking aspects of life. Their aim is to provoke introspection on our personal flaws and warn of the perils of obsession and ambition. Tragically, some view their very presence as a sign of ill events to come, either to their friends or enemies. Should you get to know one, though, they can make for surprisingly deep conversation once you get past their morose exterior.</p>", "chat": "", "unidentified": ""}, "source": "Core Rules", "identifier": "bard-tragedian", "classIdentifier": "bard", "classDetails": "<h3>Bardic Archetype: Tragedian</h3><p><i>Unlock:</i> Have the Bard Starter Abilities.</p><hr/><p>&#x1F193; Given Abilities: @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.4A26NHYUBD8OXCX5]{Theme: Mortality}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.M7ONN7XQ5CD8VK24]{Commiseration}</p><hr/><h3>Tragedian Abilities</h3><p>When taking a level in Tragedian, you may choose from the following abilities: </p><hr/><p>Options: @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.PDP9D8MMKDY2DZSL]{Star-Crossed Duel}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.X7GBQG8CSADQYOZH]{Blood-Soaked Hands}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.9KHMDNUC50478I0D]{Untimely Remorse}, @Compendium[undertaking-homebrew.abilities.AI1FILJPEB8JVZ6L]{The Bell Tolls}</p>"}, "effects": [], "folder": null, "sort": 0, "ownership": {"default": 0}, "flags": {}, "_id": "KWI7SOKT0YDM3U7C", "_stats": {"systemId": "undertaking", "systemVersion": "1.0.0", "coreVersion": "11.304"}}
